.TH "BB" "1" "Mar 2026" "bb" "Bitbucket CLI"

.SH NAME
bb-pipeline-log - Show the log for one pipeline step


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBbb pipeline log  [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Show the raw log for a pipeline step. If the pipeline has exactly one step, bb selects it automatically. Otherwise pass --step with a step UUID or name.


.SH OPTIONS
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for log

.PP
\fB--host\fP=""
	Bitbucket host to use

.PP
\fB--jq\fP=""
	Filter JSON output using a jq expression

.PP
\fB--json\fP[=""]
	Output JSON with the specified comma-separated fields, or '*' for all fields

.PP
\fB--repo\fP=""
	Bitbucket repository target as , /, or a repository URL

.PP
\fB--step\fP=""
	Pipeline step UUID or name when a pipeline has more than one step

.PP
\fB--workspace\fP=""
	Optional workspace slug used only to disambiguate a bare repository target


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB--no-prompt\fP[=false]
	Do not prompt for missing input, even in an interactive terminal


.SH EXAMPLE
.EX
  bb pipeline log 42 --repo workspace-slug/pipelines-repo-slug
  bb pipeline log 42 --repo workspace-slug/pipelines-repo-slug --step '{step-uuid}'
  bb pipeline log 42 --repo workspace-slug/pipelines-repo-slug --json pipeline,step,log
.EE


.SH SEE ALSO
\fBbb-pipeline(1)\fP


